# lj/charmmfsw/coul/long correctness test (Step 4: pair_lj_charmmfsw_coul_long_omp verification)
# PairLJCharmmfswCoulLong : public Pair (KSPACE package). CHARMM force-switched LJ
# (separate evdwl12/evdwl6 forms with denom_lj12/denom_lj6, plus forcelj switch1
# for rsq > cut_lj_innersq) combined with Ewald-softcore-free coul/long (same A1-A5
# table/direct branches as lj/charmm/coul/long, already ported in
# pair_lj_charmm_coul_long_omp.cpp). cut_lj_inner=3.0 < cut_lj=4.0 (< L/2 = 5.04 with
# this box, including 0.3 skin) keeps both the switching (rsq > cut_lj_innersq) and
# non-switching LJ branches exercised, and both the table and direct coul branches
# (ncoultablebits default). Requires a kspace_style for g_ewald; ewald avoids any
# FFT dependency.

